The paper focuses on the optimization of a cyber-physical system for autonomous electric mobility on demand, which involves the management of charging and dispatching processes. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with decision-making and optimization, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of fog computing and queuing models also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the investigation of rare critical events could place the paper in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
